                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d448">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2738: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Forbes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-18T12:00:00+09:00"
                            >November 18, 1931—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received November 18—7:07
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>222. The Military Attaché is informed by the General Staff here that the
                    dispatching of an additional division to Manchuria is being considered. The
                    Military Attaché is apparently of the opinion that approval has already been
                    given this movement. It is stated also by the General Staff that three more air
                    squadrons have gone to Manchuria.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Forbes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
